Just Friday, columnist Charles Krauthammer and Weekly Standard editor William Kristol called on Bush to withdraw the Miers nomination, with Krauthammer deriding her selection as ``scandalous'' and ``a joke.'' Another icon of the conservative movement, former Judge Robert H. Bork, denounced it as ``a disaster on every level.'' At every point where the White House has hoped it might have turned the corner, it has run into more flak from the right. 